
Modes for Mods:


---------------------------------------------------------

A clean, ad-free curation newsletter focused on linking to well-established, well-lawyered articles is 
the safest, most legally bulletproof method to actively participate in political accountability without 
exposing yourself to ruinous litigation. By serving as an aggregator who curates existing investigative 
reporting, you shield yourself behind the legal departments of major news institutions like The Washington 
Post or ProPublica while still advancing the democratic causes you care about.

Why a Curation Model Safeguards You

No Defamation Exposure: You are not making original, unverified assertions of fact. You are pointing readers to 
statements that have already passed corporate legal review.

No Copyright Violations: You are not copy-pasting full text. Providing a short, unique summary alongside a direct 
outbound link falls squarely under safe digital practices and drives traffic to the primary source.

No Ad Clutter: Operating via an email-first format completely removes the reliance on broken, privacy-invasive banner 
ad networks that ruin traditional news websites.

A Model for Legal Accountability Curation

To hold political actors accountable to their shifting stances without getting sued, focus entirely on archival 
documentation. You can structure your publication around tracking public statements and official records:

The "Receipts" Archive: Create a recurring segment that pairs past actions with current rhetoric. If a figure 
attempts to distance themselves from extreme positions, publish the official, unedited voting record or public 
transcript side-by-side with their new statement.

Tracking Court Records: Curate entries directly from public federal court dockets, unsealed indictments, 
and congressional findings. Facts derived from official government proceedings are heavily protected from 
libel claims under the "fair report privilege."


