browser localStorage or IndexedDB for offline train use?

To achieve seamless reading on the Q train, storing the text payload in IndexedDB is significantly 
better than localStorage. localStorage has a strict limit of around 5MB, which will quickly choke 
on full-text news articles. IndexedDB can store hundreds of megabytes of structured data directly 
on the device.

The most reliable, industry-standard way to manage IndexedDB in a React application is by using a 
small, lightweight library called Dexie.js.













